SIMPLE: feint
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Feint
<hw>Feint</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>feint</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>feindre</ets> to feign. See <er>Feign</er>.]</ety>
<def>Feigned; counterfeit.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dressed up into any <qex>feint</qex> appearance of it.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Feint
<hw>Feint</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>feinte</ets>, fr.
<ets>feint</ets>. See <er>Feint</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>That which is feigned; an assumed or false appearance; a pretense;
a stratagem; a fetch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Courtley's letter is but a <qex>feint</qex> to get off.</q>
<rj><qau>Spectator.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mock blow or attack on one part when another part
is intended to be struck; -- said of certain movements in fencing,
boxing, war, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feint</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Feint
<hw>Feint</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a feint, or mock
attack.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feitsui</ent>⟦br⟧
